Background

		Mr. Robert E. Switz, also known as Bob, served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of ADC Telecommunications Inc., from August 2003 to December 2010. Mr. Switz served as the Chief Financial Officer of ADC Telecommunications Inc. from January 1994 to August 2003 and served as its Executive Vice President until August 2003. He served as Senior Vice President of ADC Telecommunications Inc. from May 1997 to 2001 and served as its Vice President from January 1994 ... to 1997. He joined ADC Telecommunications Inc. in January 1994. He served as a Fund Manager of ADC Ventures. He served as the President and Chief Financial Officer of the Broadband Access and Transport Group from November 2000 to April 2001. He was employed by Burr-Brown Corporation and served as Vice President of European Operations, Ventures & Finance (Chief Financial Officer) and Director, Ventures & Systems Business from 1988 to 1994. He held senior financial management positions at PepsiCo, AMF and Olin Corporation. He has been Chairman of Micron Technology, Inc. since February 2012. He served as the Chairman of ADC Ventures since May 2001. He served as the Chairman of ADC Telecommunications Inc. from July 2008 to December 2010. Mr. Switz has been Director of Marvell Technology Group Ltd. since May 1, 2016. He has been Independent Director of Micron Technology, Inc. since February 7, 2006. He has been a Director of GT Advanced Technologies Inc. since May 2011, Gigamon Inc. since June 11, 2015 and Recombinetics, Inc., since May 18, 2016. He serves as a Director for Axient Communications, Pulse Electronics Corporation and GTAT Corporation (formerly, GT Solar Incorporated). He served as a Director of Cyan, Inc. from March 2011 to August 3, 2015. He served as a Director of Broadcom Corporation from May 28, 2003 to February 1, 2016 and served as its Lead Independent Director from May 2014 to February 1, 2016. He served as a Director of ADC Telecommunications Inc. from August 13, 2003 to 2010. He served as a Director of Leap Wireless International Inc. from July 28, 2011 to March 13, 2014. He served as a Director of Enventis Corporation from 1999 to April 24, 2006. He served as a Director of Hickory Tech Corp. from 1999 to April 24, 2006. He served as a Director of Adaytum, Inc. He served as a Director of Adaytum Software, Inc. since June 2000. In 1999, he was a recipient of the Chief Financial Officer Excellence award from Chief Financial Officer Magazine and Arthur Andersen. Mr. Switz holds an MBA in Finance from the University of Bridgeport as well as a B.S. in Marketing/Economics and Business Administration from Quinnipiac University in Hamden, Connecticut.Read Full Background




